reviews.review_text: Great Show! Thanks for another great Show!    You can hear each and every word.  The audience is in just the right groove.  I don't think it was He's Gone ->Bob Star- I think it was more like Bob was Gone  hahaha.

The boys were on- high energy show Excellent audience- no talking into or distracting yelling from people near the mic's.  Notes say 15' in front of SBD- was a mic-stand used?  I'd like to know more about what it was like to tape this show...

Superior performance with the exception of Brown-eyed Women, in which Jerry forgets almost every word.

Ship o'Fools is heartfelt with emotional intonation- a statement on playing a war memorial?

Excellent drums out of the Bobstar, and nice long jamming Space.

Charlie Miller please write a biography recounting your experiences as a taper.

BEW Jerry's mIc was malfunctioning. I was at this show and have a master recording. Another reviewer on a different recording also recalls this. In my opinion, when the mic goes out Jerry and Phil step up and play a great series of leads. Then the crowd gets revved up once the crew gets the new mic set.
Overall a great show, was one of the best most fun early 80's tours for me and my crew.
